<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-15T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-15T19:00:00-05:00" n="906" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d906">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13G30a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to Mexico.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-15T19:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 15, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>246. Please deliver the following message to Vice Consul Silliman: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Please say to General Carranza that the President is arranging to
                                    withdraw the American troops from Vera Cruz and desires that
                                    some responsible authority be named to whom the custom house may
                                    be turned over; also officials to whom authority in the city may
                                    be delivered. Inquire whether it is within the power of the
                                    Federal authorities to designate the officials or whether it is
                                    desired that the American commanding officer shall select
                                    eligible residents of Vera Cruz to exercise authority until the
                                    ordinary processes can be utilized.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>